Larval hosts: This is another Pinaceae feeder, but prefers balsam fir (
Abies balsamea
(L.) P. Mill) and western hemlock (
Tsuga heterophylla (Raf.) Sarg.
); other hosts include white spruce (
Picea glauca (Moench) Voss
), Douglas fir (
Pseudotsuga menziesii (Mirb.) Franco
), Pacific Silver fir (
A. amabilis (Dougl. ex Loud) Dougl. ex Forbes
), grand fir (
A. grandis (Dougl. ex D. Don) Lindl.
), sitka spruce (
Picea sitchensis (Bong.) Carr.
), red spruce (
Picea rubens Sarg.
), black spruce (
Picea mariana (Mill.)
B. S. P.), mountain hemlock (
Tsuga mertensiana (Bong.) Carr.
), tamarack (
Larix laricina (Du Roi) K. Koch
), and subalpine fir (
A. lasiocarpa (Hook.) Nutt.
). These hosts are arranged by number of larvae collected on each host (
Prentice 1962
